parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the coil spring can cause loss of control, accidents, or injuries, especially if it occurs while driving. Additionally, it can lead to punctured tires, which can further compromise vehicle safety.
The failure of the front suspension ball joints can cause excessive tire wear, vibration in the steering, and potential loss of steering control, which can lead to accidents or injuries.
Vibration issues can cause discomfort, distraction, and loss of control while driving, which can lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Vibration in the rear and right front of the vehicle
severe vibration in the front of the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission issues can cause loss of control, accidents, or injuries, especially if the vehicle becomes stuck in gear or unable to shift gears.

The failure of the 5R55W transmission can cause the vehicle to hesitate, buck, or lose power when accelerating, shifting gears, or reversing, which can lead to accidents, loss of control, or injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle hesitates or bucks when accelerating from a dead stop
surges backwards when put in reverse

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the liftgate can cause injury or damage, especially if it shatters or breaks suddenly.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Failure Due to Sudden Loss of Oil
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden loss of oil can cause engine failure, leading to a loss of power and control, which can result in accidents or leave the driver stranded.
A gasoline leak from the fuel tank can cause a fire hazard, potentially leading to injury or death.
symptoms: liquid dripping from the fuel tank
saturated seals and tank with a dark gasoline-smelling liquid.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the engine coolant hose clamp can cause coolant to leak out, leading to engine overheating, loss of power, and difficulty controlling the vehicle, which can result in accidents.
